(6687, 'x8apm', '2016-03-17 21:06:45', 't_mid.1458212018597:162fcbb7fa09e4fb37', 'o', '4', 'mvasantos@uplbosa.org', '[Staff Comment]: @channel draft reply. i\'ll ask NMC for her comments re this inquiry.\r\n\r\nHi Jean. We\'re very sorry to hear this. Unfortunately, our accounting and auditing rules only permit currently registered students from availing student loans. Also, the emergency student fund may only be claimed by each student once. Regarding the cash loans with academic standing requirements, these are requirements set by the donors which are outlined in their memorandums of agreement with UPLB.\r\n\r\nSince your friend is currently employed, we advise you to coordinate with your friend\'s current employer regarding this situation especially because what she is going through right now happened during her employment. They may be able to provide her financial assistance or they may have loans for their employees.\r\n\r\nIf you are willing and if you are qualified, you may apply for a loan (under your name) so you can lend money to your friend.\r\n\r\nThank you.', '', '', ''),
