(6947, 'pw6n9', '2016-04-14 13:29:57', 't_mid.1460601756451:01f4a0835943050259', 'i', '3', '', 'Good afternoon OSA, I have an issue to share with you regarding the hacking of UPLB-based organizations.\n\n Last night my facebook account was hacked, specifically to enter and manipulate the facebook page of my organization UP MunSci Alumni Society, a UPLB-based socio-civic organization. My fb page is linked to my yahoomail since it is the one I used in creating it years ago. However, the hacker was able to add his/her UP email address on the list of email addresses that are affiliated in my fb account. Because of this, he/she was able to enter my fb account, alter the profile picture and cover photo of our org page, then deactivate my account. Fortunately, I was able to retrieve my account due to yahoo mail security features. The same thing has already happed to at least three other UPLB organizations, namely the UPLB Society of Electrical Engineering Students, the UPLB Engineering Society, and the Filipiana Dance Troupe.\n\nThe email address used was msmontala@up.edu.ph\n\nWith this, may I know if this account is a legitimate UP mail. And if so, what can I do about it? I believe this is a very serious and alarming matter. Thank you and God bless :)', '19', 'm_mid.1460611777176:2addd06e85970c3f10', '{"name":"Paolo Yves De Silos","email":null,"fbuserid":"100000169940410"}'),
(6948, '9kd65', '2016-04-14 15:19:20', 't_mid.1460605830741:adaf2cf44291260610', 'o', '4', 'mvasantos@uplbosa.org', 'Hi Izza! Here\'s a copy of the academic calendar: https://www.uplbosa.org/download/acadcal1516. Thanks!', '', '', ''),
(6949, 'm7yew', '2016-04-14 15:28:51', 't_mid.1460601756451:01f4a0835943050259', 'o', '4', 'mvasantos@uplbosa.org', 'Regarding the UBU Language and Culture Camp 2016, we advise you to get in touch with the the person or office who posted the announcement. We\'ll get back to you at a later time regarding your second inquiry.', '', '', ''),
(6950, 'm7yew', '2016-04-14 15:40:45', 't_mid.1460601756451:01f4a0835943050259', 'o', '4', 'mvasantos@uplbosa.org', 'Regarding the hacking of Facebook accounts, please be advised that it is the responsibility of the account holders to ensure that their accounts are secure. We advise students to never share their password to anyone, not even to friends, family, or significant other. Likewise, students using shared computers are advised to log out from their accounts after using a shared computer. Among the things we share to students to protect their accounts are:\r\n* change password regularly\r\n* do not use the same password for online accounts\r\n* use a password that cannot be easily guessed such as birth dates or monthsaries\r\n* never share passwords to anyone\r\n* log out from all accounts after using a shared computer\r\n\r\nBasing on your report, we reckon that the hacker was able to access your Facebook account because s/he knows the password of your account. The only way to add an email address to a Facebook account is to update the profile and input the current password of the logged in user. We advise you to change your password.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, we cannot give you any information regarding the email address you provided.\r\n\r\nFor any other security issues regarding your Facebook account, we advise you to get in touch with Facebook directly. We may only be able to assist you regarding OSA services and systems.\r\n\r\nThank you.', '', '', ''),
